The paper deals with computational complexity, graph theory, metric embeddings, and information theory. The use of the Unique Games Conjecture and probabilistically checkable proof systems suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The construction of integrality gap instances and the study of negative type metrics suggest a connection to graph theory (cs.DS, cs.CG) and metric embeddings (cs.LG).
